HEADWORD: Dingo
<hw>Din"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
wild dog found in Australia, but supposed to have introduced at a very
early period. It has a wolflike face, bushy tail, and a reddish brown
color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

